data.description: This lovely 1918 craftsman 3 bedroom bungalow features many delightful period details like stained glass windows and built-ins and tons of extra storage space.  There is a detached garage, a nice yard with mature plantings, a super large undeveloped basement, and a very long driveway. There is some deferred maintenance, but the property is fully livable and charming. There is an extra bedroom-sized room at the rear of the house, and huge potential for whomever buyers the property.  The front yard is planted with drought-tolerant plants, and the neighborhood is bursting with vital artistic energy.  Convenient to all kinds of commute options, freeway access, schools, and more, this is a very wonderful place to call home.
